Mark P. Frissora: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 7:32 AM ET
Hotels, Restaurants and Leisure

Company Overview of Caesars Entertainment Corporation



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Mark P. Frissora  President, CEO & Director, Caesars Entertainment CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships62$9,510,932As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Mark P. Frissora has been the Chief Executive Officer and President at Caesars Entertainment Corporation since July 1, 2015. Mr. Frissora serves as an Interim President of HERC. He serves as the President and Manager of Caesars Entertainment Resort Properties, LLC. Mr. Frissora served as the Chief Executive Officer at The Hertz Corporation since January 01, 2007 until September 7, 2014. Mr. Frissora served as Chief Executive Officer and Executive Chairman of Hertz ... Global Holdings, Inc. from January 1, 2007 to September 8, 2014. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Tenneco Inc. from April 1999 to July 19, 2006 and also served as its President until July 19, 2006; he served as President of the automotive operations of Tenneco from April 1999 to July 19, 2006 and from 1996 to April 1999, Mr. Frissora held various positions within firm's automotive operations, including Senior Vice President and General Manager of the worldwide original equipment business from 1998 to March 1999. He joined Tenneco Inc. in 1996 as Vice President of North American emissions control operations for Walker Manufacturing. Mr. Frissora served as a Vice President of Aeroquip Vickers Corporation from 1991 to 1996. From 1987 to 1991, he held various management positions at Philips N.V., including Director of Marketing and Director of Sales. Mr. Frissora was with General Electric Co. for 10 years in positions of increasing responsibility in brand management, marketing and sales. He has over 28 years of consumer and automotive-related experience in both aftermarket and original equipment businesses. Mr. Frissora served as the Chairman of Tenneco Inc from March 2000 to July 19, 2006 and served as its Director from November 1999 to July 19, 2006. He has been a Director at Caesars Entertainment Corporation since February 2015 and Delphi Automotive PLC since December 2009. He served as Director of Walgreens Boots Alliance, Inc., from December 2009 to April 1, 2015. He served as a Director of FMC Corp., from January 1, 2004 to August 18, 2006. He served as an Executive Director of Hertz Global Holdings, Inc. since July 19, 2006. He served as a Director of NCR Corp., from June 5, 2002 to November 18, 2009. Mr. Frissora is a member of The Business Roundtable and the World Economic Forum's Automotive Board of Governors. Mr. Frissora holds a B.A. degree from The Ohio State University and has completed executive development programs at the University of Pennsylvania’s Wharton School and the Thunderbird International School of Management.Read Full Background




